content.htmlText:
Given its geographical location, the Ternes district does not escape Parisian chic; major brands jostle there to offer their windows. But despite this luxurious side, the neighborhood remains very warm day and night.

The village of Les Ternes is known as one of the most commercial and lively in the city. There are all sorts of people, and especially merchants.

In addition to commercial spaces, flower markets and green spaces, the neighborhood allows you to discover the Cernuschi Museum and Parc Monceau.

A detailed neighborhood guide will be offered for your stay:)

verifiedHelpModalContent.title: How listings are verified
verifiedHelpModalContent.body:
Listings are verified after the Host submits photos or videos to show their place is where they say it is––and they have access to it.

In some cases, a listing can be verified if guest reviews confirm its location, the Host provides extra documents, or if the listing is managed by a company that signs an agreement.

This process has safeguards, but is not a guarantee that every detail on the listing is accurate. Learn about listing verification

PEREIRE STATION 2 MINUTE AWAY:

The Parisian metro station of Pereire is located on Line 3 of the Paris Metro. It is connected by RER C, Transilien line L as well as buses 84, buses 92, bus 93 and bus 341.

htmlDescription.htmlText:
This 25 m2 studio is perched at the top of a traditional Parisian building in the Ternes district. Two large windows print views of the iconic landscape of Haussmannian urban planning, typical of the city.

In the heart of the 17th and close to Paris and not far from Place de l 'Etoile, the apartment makes it easy to access tourist attractions and business districts on the right bank of Paris.

The space
Welcome!

This 25m2 studio is at the top of a traditional Parisian building in the Ternes district. It overlooks iconic Haussmannian urban planning, through two large windows that create views of Rue des Courcelles.

Located in the heart of the 17th arrondissement, close to Paris and not far from Place de l 'Etoile, the apartment makes it easy to access the tourist attractions of the right bank (Arc de Triomphe, Batignolles...) but also to the business districts of La Défense and Levallois.

The studio offers a moment of rest after a day of wanderings in Paris, and the amenities needed to cook or work from home.

A piano has been staying there for twenty years, he accompanied the host to his visit from childhood to adulthood and offers you a musical getaway under the rooftops of Paris.

Guest access
No elevator

Other things to note
Special filter for shower which prevents limestone to come through the water so your hair and skin can shine brighter :-) !

No elevator 6th floor

Registration number
7511705800911
